Imo State chairman of All Progressive Grand Alliance (APGA), Dr Henry Okafor has resigned his position with immediate effect. Okafor made the disclosure in a letter addressed to the deputy chairman of the party in the state. He failed to state the reasons for his resignation but thanked the party for the opportunity to serve. Okafor, former Managing Director of ISOPADEC, announced his resignation from the party and from his ward at Ossemotoo Enuigbo in Oguta local government. He said the resignation was as a result of developments in the party and support from his family. Okafor, a House of Representatives aspirant during the 2019 general election, prayed for success for the party in its future endeavours. Only last month, state chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Barrister Charles Ezekwem also resigned his membership of the party. Okafor’s resignation may not be unconnected with the emergence of Senator Hope Uzodinma as governor of Imo State.